---
---

<section id="features" aria-labelledby="features-heading">

  <div class="wrap ft-head" data-reveal>
    <span class="eyebrow"><span class="eyebrow-dot"></span>Why it works</span>
    <h2 id="features-heading" class="ft-h2">The AI already has your context.<br>You just don't have to write it.</h2>
  </div>

  <!-- Row 1: Context → full-width alternating -->
  <div class="ft-row ft-row-a" data-reveal>
    <div class="ftr-visual">
      <!-- Terminal-style context display -->
      <div class="ft-terminal">
        <div class="ftt-bar">
          <span class="fttb-dot" style="background:#FF5F57"></span>
          <span class="fttb-dot" style="background:#FFBD2E"></span>
          <span class="fttb-dot" style="background:#28C840"></span>
          <span class="fttb-title mono">context-engine.log</span>
        </div>
        <div class="ftt-body mono">
          <div class="fttl"><span class="fttl-key">active_app</span><span class="fttl-sep"> = </span><span class="fttl-val">Xcode.app</span></div>
          <div class="fttl"><span class="fttl-key">lang</span><span class="fttl-sep"> = </span><span class="fttl-val">swift</span></div>
          <div class="fttl"><span class="fttl-key">framework</span><span class="fttl-sep"> = </span><span class="fttl-val">swiftui</span></div>
          <div class="fttl"><span class="fttl-key">selected_lines</span><span class="fttl-sep"> = </span><span class="fttl-val">42</span></div>
          <div class="fttl"><span class="fttl-key">clipboard[0]</span><span class="fttl-sep"> = </span><span class="fttl-val">UserDefaults.standard.string(forKey:)</span></div>
          <div class="fttl"><span class="fttl-key">clipboard[1]</span><span class="fttl-sep"> = </span><span class="fttl-val">@AppStorage("onboarding_done")</span></div>
          <div class="fttl fttl-dim"><span class="fttl-key">scope</span><span class="fttl-sep"> = </span><span class="fttl-val">mobile-dev · ios-engineering</span></div>
          <div class="fttl fttl-dim"><span class="fttl-key">style_profile</span><span class="fttl-sep"> = </span><span class="fttl-val">Engineering</span></div>
          <div class="fttl fttl-hi">
            <span class="fttl-tag">
              <iconify-icon icon="lucide:check-circle-2" style="font-size:11px;vertical-align:middle;margin-right:3px;" aria-hidden="true"></iconify-icon>
              injected into assembler
            </span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="ftr-text">
      <span class="ftr-n mono">01</span>
      <h3 class="ftr-h3">Context you never have to write.</h3>
      <p class="ftr-body">
        The Context Engine reads your active application, selected text, and clipboard history before assembling any prompt. Coding in Xcode with a SwiftUI file open? It knows. Writing in Notion? It adjusts tone. The pipeline always knows what you were working on — without you ever saying it.
      </p>
      <div class="ftr-detail">
        <div class="ftrd-item">
          <iconify-icon icon="lucide:check" style="font-size:14px;color:var(--acc);flex-shrink:0;margin-top:1px;" aria-hidden="true"></iconify-icon>
          Active app and language detected automatically
        </div>
        <div class="ftrd-item">
          <iconify-icon icon="lucide:check" style="font-size:14px;color:var(--acc);flex-shrink:0;margin-top:1px;" aria-hidden="true"></iconify-icon>
          Clipboard history ring (last 8 items)
        </div>
        <div class="ftrd-item">
          <iconify-icon icon="lucide:check" style="font-size:14px;color:var(--acc);flex-shrink:0;margin-top:1px;" aria-hidden="true"></iconify-icon>
          Accessibility permission is read-only, sandboxed
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Row 2: Styles → visual right -->
  <div class="ft-row ft-row-b" data-reveal>
    <div class="ftr-text">
      <span class="ftr-n mono">02</span>
      <h3 class="ftr-h3">Seven optimization styles. Immediately.</h3>
      <p class="ftr-body">
        Engineering adds role specification, constraint enumeration, format requirements, and test stubs. Research adds academic framing and source awareness. Content adds narrative structure and audience tone. You switch styles with one click — and the same rough input produces a completely different, equally precise result.
      </p>
      <div class="ftr-detail">
        <div class="ftrd-item">
          <iconify-icon icon="lucide:check" style="font-size:14px;color:var(--acc);flex-shrink:0;margin-top:1px;" aria-hidden="true"></iconify-icon>
          7 built-in styles: General, Engineering, Research, Content, Analysis, Academic, Creative
        </div>
        <div class="ftrd-item">
          <iconify-icon icon="lucide:check" style="font-size:14px;color:var(--acc);flex-shrink:0;margin-top:1px;" aria-hidden="true"></iconify-icon>
          Custom templates you define, save, and reuse
        </div>
        <div class="ftrd-item">
          <iconify-icon icon="lucide:check" style="font-size:14px;color:var(--acc);flex-shrink:0;margin-top:1px;" aria-hidden="true"></iconify-icon>
          Same input, different style = completely different optimized output
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="ftr-visual">
      <!-- Style comparison -->
      <div class="ft-styles-demo">
        <div class="ftsd-input">
          <span class="ftsd-label mono">You type</span>
          <p class="ftsd-text">write a test for the login method</p>
        </div>
        <div class="ftsd-outputs">
          <div class="ftsd-out">
            <span class="ftsd-tag mono">Engineering</span>
            <p class="ftsd-out-text mono">You are a senior backend QA engineer. Task: write an integration test suite for the login endpoint. Constraints: Jest, supertest, test success (200), bad credentials (401), rate limit (429), locked account (423)...</p>
          </div>
          <div class="ftsd-out ftsd-out-b">
            <span class="ftsd-tag mono">General</span>
            <p class="ftsd-out-text mono">Write a comprehensive test for the login function covering the happy path and at least three failure scenarios with appropriate assertions...</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Row 3: Speed + privacy → visual left -->
  <div class="ft-row ft-row-a" data-reveal>
    <div class="ftr-visual">
      <div class="ft-spec-grid">
        <div class="ftsg-item">
          <span class="ftsg-n">140ms</span>
          <span class="ftsg-l mono">avg pipeline end-to-end</span>
        </div>
        <div class="ftsg-item">
          <span class="ftsg-n">0</span>
          <span class="ftsg-l mono">external servers before your AI</span>
        </div>
        <div class="ftsg-item">
          <span class="ftsg-n">Local</span>
          <span class="ftsg-l mono">full Ollama support, offline capable</span>
        </div>
        <div class="ftsg-item">
          <span class="ftsg-n">1</span>
          <span class="ftsg-l mono">permission required (Accessibility, read-only)</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="ftr-text">
      <span class="ftr-n mono">03</span>
      <h3 class="ftr-h3">Faster than you can blink. Private by design.</h3>
      <p class="ftr-body">
        The entire 7-stage pipeline runs on your Mac in under 200ms. Your prompts never reach an external server until they touch your chosen AI provider — and with Ollama, that never happens at all. One read-only Accessibility permission. No telemetry. No logging. No account required for the app itself.
      </p>
      <div class="ftr-detail">
        <div class="ftrd-item">
          <iconify-icon icon="lucide:check" style="font-size:14px;color:var(--acc);flex-shrink:0;margin-top:1px;" aria-hidden="true"></iconify-icon>
          Zero telemetry — not even anonymous usage data
        </div>
        <div class="ftrd-item">
          <iconify-icon icon="lucide:check" style="font-size:14px;color:var(--acc);flex-shrink:0;margin-top:1px;" aria-hidden="true"></iconify-icon>
          Signed with Developer ID, notarized by Apple
        </div>
        <div class="ftrd-item">
          <iconify-icon icon="lucide:check" style="font-size:14px;color:var(--acc);flex-shrink:0;margin-top:1px;" aria-hidden="true"></iconify-icon>
          Works fully offline with any Ollama model
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

</section>

<style>
  #features { padding: 80px 0 0; }

  .ft-head { margin-bottom: 64px; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 16px; }
  .ft-h2 { font-size: clamp(26px, 3.8vw, 46px); font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: -0.045em; line-height: 1.1; color: var(--ink); }

  /* Alternating rows */
  .ft-row {
    display: grid; gap: 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--bdr);
    align-items: stretch;
  }
  .ft-row:last-child { border-bottom: 1px solid var(--bdr); }

  .ft-row-a { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; }
  .ft-row-b { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; }

  .ftr-visual {
    padding: 56px 48px;
    background: var(--bg2);
    display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;
  }
  .ft-row-a .ftr-visual { border-right: 1px solid var(--bdr); }
  .ft-row-b .ftr-visual { border-left: 1px solid var(--bdr); order: 2; }

  .ftr-text {
    padding: 56px 52px;
    display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 20px;
  }
  .ft-row-b .ftr-text { order: 1; }

  .ftr-n { font-size: 11px; font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: 0.08em; color: var(--acc); }
  .ftr-h3 { font-size: clamp(20px, 2.5vw, 28px); font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: -0.035em; color: var(--ink); line-height: 1.2; }
  .ftr-body { font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.8; color: var(--mid); }

  .ftr-detail { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 10px; margin-top: 4px; }
  .ftrd-item {
    display: flex; align-items: flex-start; gap: 10px;
    font-size: 13px; line-height: 1.5; color: var(--mid);
  }
  .ftrd-item svg { flex-shrink: 0; margin-top: 1px; }

  /* Terminal widget */
  .ft-terminal {
    width: 100%; max-width: 460px;
    background: var(--dk); border-radius: 10px;
    overflow: hidden;
    box-shadow: 0 8px 24px rgba(0,0,0,0.15), 0 2px 4px rgba(0,0,0,0.08);
  }
  .ftt-bar {
    display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 6px;
    padding: 10px 14px; background: var(--dk2);
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.06);
  }
  .fttb-dot { width: 10px; height: 10px; border-radius: 50%; }
  .fttb-title { font-size: 11px; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.35); letter-spacing: 0.04em; margin-left: 8px; }

  .ftt-body { padding: 16px; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 5px; }
  .fttl { display: flex; gap: 0; font-size: 11px; line-height: 1.6; }
  .fttl-key { color: rgba(100,160,255,0.7); }
  .fttl-sep { color: rgba(255,255,255,0.25); padding: 0 4px; }
  .fttl-val { color: rgba(255,255,255,0.75); }
  .fttl-dim .fttl-key,
  .fttl-dim .fttl-val { opacity: .5; }
  .fttl-tag { color: var(--acc-hi); font-size: 11px; margin-top: 4px; opacity: .8; }

  /* Style demo */
  .ft-styles-demo { width: 100%; max-width: 460px; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 16px; }

  .ftsd-input {
    padding: 16px; background: var(--bg3); border-radius: 8px;
    border: 1px solid var(--bdr-hi);
    display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 6px;
  }
  .ftsd-label { font-size: 9px; font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: 0.1em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--dim); }
  .ftsd-text  { font-size: 14px; color: var(--ink2); font-weight: 500; }

  .ftsd-outputs { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 8px; }
  .ftsd-out {
    padding: 14px 16px; border-radius: 8px;
    background: var(--card); border: 1px solid var(--bdr);
    display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 6px;
  }
  .ftsd-out-b { opacity: .55; }
  .ftsd-tag { font-size: 9px; font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: 0.1em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--acc); }
  .ftsd-out-text { font-size: 11px; line-height: 1.6; color: var(--mid); white-space: pre-wrap; }

  /* Spec grid */
  .ft-spec-grid {
    display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 1px; background: var(--bdr);
    border: 1px solid var(--bdr); border-radius: 10px;
    overflow: hidden; width: 100%; max-width: 460px;
  }
  .ftsg-item {
    padding: 24px 20px; background: var(--bg);
    display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 6px;
    transition: background .15s;
  }
  .ftsg-item:hover { background: var(--bg3); }
  .ftsg-n { font-size: 28px; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: -0.05em; color: var(--ink); line-height: 1; }
  .ftsg-l { font-size: 11px; color: var(--dim); letter-spacing: 0.03em; }

  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .ft-row-a, .ft-row-b { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .ft-row-a .ftr-visual, .ft-row-b .ftr-visual { border-right: none; border-left: none; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--bdr); order: 0; }
    .ft-row-b .ftr-text { order: 0; }
    .ftr-text, .ftr-visual { padding: 36px 20px; }
  }
</style>
